from surprise import Reader, Dataset, SVD, NormalPredictor, Reader, accuracy
from surprise.model_selection import train_test_split, cross_validate, GridSearchCV
from surprise import accuracy

reader = Reader(rating_scale=(1, 5))
data = Dataset.load_from_df(dt[['user_id','item_id','rating']], reader)

# Do Some cross Validation
# define hyperparamater
hyperparam =  {
    "n_epochs": [5, 10], 
    "lr_all": [0.002, 0.005], 
    "reg_all": [0.4, 0.6]
}

gs =GridSearchCV(SVD, param_grid=hyperparam, measures=["rmse","mae"], cv=3)
gs.fit(data)


    





















In[]:






print(gs.best_score["rmse"])
print(gs.best_params["rmse"])

























0.9642924518406115
{'n_epochs': 10, 'lr_all': 0.005, 'reg_all': 0.4}





















In[]:






trainset,testset = train_test_split(data, test_size=0.2)
clf = SVD(**gs.best_params["rmse"])
clf.fit(trainset)
predictions = clf.test(testset)
accuracy.rmse(predictions)
accuracy.mae(predictions)
